The paper deals with the problem of optimising plans, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence and planning (cs.AI). The use of ordering relations and the modification of action ordering is a key concept in planning languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of optimising parallel execution time is related to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the proposed algorithms, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
